SIMPLE: inexpert
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inexpert
<hw>In`ex*pert"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inexpertus</ets> inexperienced: cf. F. <ets>inexpert</ets>. See
<er>In-</er> not, and <er>Expert</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Destitute of experience or of much experience.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not expert; not skilled; destitute of knowledge or
dexterity derived from practice.</def> <rj><au>Akenside.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inexpertness</ent>⟦br⟧
